name: BeeKay
title: Excellent yogurt starter culture!
review: This is a great starter for the 24-hour probiotic-filled yogurt I made!It turned out perfectly.Once it ferments for the 24-hours it is sugar-free, lactose-free, and has more healthy probiotics than actual probiotics. It is nice and tangy and creamy. If you want it to be thicker, strain the yogurt in the fridge for 6-8 hours to drain off the extra liquid.Either way, it’s so delicious!Enjoy!

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on July 27, 2021
name: Len Burman
title: Starter makes clotted unappealing yogurt
review: I’ve made two batches of yogurt using this starter. The yogurt tastes okay, but the consistency is clotted and unappealing, almost like cottage cheese. I’ve been making yogurt using the same technique for many years so it is not user error. I’m using the same milk from a local farm so it must be the starter. I'm throwing out the remaining packets and returning to yogourmet brand.
